cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.LO, cs.CL, cs.PL.AI 

This paper is about a Prolog-based prototype system for programming language analysis and implementation tools. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also discusses the appropriateness of Prolog as the implementation language, which falls under the category of cs.SE (Software Engineering). The system's structure and methodologies also involve logic and reasoning, which could be categorized under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of natural language processing techniques, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper discusses the use of artificial intelligence techniques in the system, which could be categorized under cs.PL.AI (Artificial Intelligence and Programming Languages).
